cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the application of machine learning models to MRI-based connectome data, which involves both graph theory and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing connectome data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
